---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="MPhil / SCQF Level 11 | Doctoral College UK" description="DCUK's MPhil — a rigorous research degree of 18 to 24 months, credit-rated at SCQF Level 11. A standalone qualification or pathway to doctoral study. £4,800 per year.">

  <section class="bg-surface border-b border-border py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-4">Programme</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">MPhil / SCQF Level 11</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-accent font-medium mb-4">MPhil &mdash; 18 to 24 months &mdash; £4,800 per year</p>
      <p class="text-lg text-muted max-w-2xl">The DCUK MPhil is a substantive research degree for professionals who want to conduct supervised original research but are not yet ready — or do not wish — to commit to a full doctorate. Credit-rated at SCQF Level 11, it is a recognised and respected standalone qualification that can also serve as a pathway to doctoral progression.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-12">
        <div class="card text-center">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-accent mb-2">18–24 Months</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted">Part-time, flexible scheduling</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card text-center">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-accent mb-2">SCQF Level 11</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted">Credit-rated within the Scottish Credit and Qualifications Framework</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card text-center">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-accent mb-2">£4,800/yr</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted">Total £7,200–£9,600 depending on duration</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
        <div>
          <p class="section-label mb-3">About the MPhil</p>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Research at the Highest Pre-Doctoral Level</h2>
          <p class="text-muted mb-4">The Master of Philosophy is a research degree, not a taught postgraduate qualification. It requires you to design and conduct an original research project, submit a substantial thesis (typically 40,000–60,000 words), and pass an oral examination. It is a meaningful intellectual achievement and a recognised academic qualification.</p>
          <p class="text-muted mb-4">DCUK's MPhil is credit-rated at SCQF Level 11 — the level of the first year of a Scottish doctoral degree — enabling recognition and potential credit transfer within the UK higher education system.</p>
          <p class="text-muted">Successful MPhil completion may be recognised as partial credit towards DCUK doctoral programmes for candidates who subsequently wish to progress to a DBA, EdD, or Online PhD.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="section-label mb-3">Who Should Apply</p>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Is the MPhil Right for You?</h2>
          <div class="space-y-3">
            <div class="card">
              <p class="text-muted text-sm">You want to conduct rigorous original research but are not ready to commit to three or more years of doctoral study.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
              <p class="text-muted text-sm">You want a recognised research qualification to advance your professional or academic career without a full doctorate.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
              <p class="text-muted text-sm">You are testing whether doctoral-level research is for you, with the option to progress to a full doctorate if you wish.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
              <p class="text-muted text-sm">You have a specific, bounded research question that can be addressed in 18–24 months of part-time study.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Structure -->
  <section class="bg-surface border-y border-border py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-3">Programme Structure</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">18–24 Months to MPhil</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-bold mb-3 text-accent">Stage 1 (Months 1–9)</h3>
          <ul class="text-muted text-sm space-y-2">
            <li>Introduction to Research Methods module</li>
            <li>Literature review development</li>
            <li>Research design and ethics approval</li>
            <li>Research proposal submission and approval</li>
            <li>Supervision meetings (minimum 6 in first nine months)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-bold mb-3 text-accent">Stage 2 (Months 10–18/24)</h3>
          <ul class="text-muted text-sm space-y-2">
            <li>Data collection and analysis</li>
            <li>Thesis writing with supervisor feedback</li>
            <li>Progress review at month 12</li>
            <li>Thesis submission (40,000–60,000 words)</li>
            <li>Oral examination (viva voce)</li>
            <li>Award of MPhil</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Requirements -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-3">Entry Requirements</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">What We Look For</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">Academic</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">Bachelor's degree at 2:1 or above, or equivalent. A postgraduate qualification is not required, though applicants with a Master's degree are welcome. Strong professional portfolios are considered alongside academic qualifications.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">Professional</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">Relevant professional experience is valued but not strictly required at the level demanded by our doctoral programmes. The MPhil is appropriate for earlier-career professionals as well as senior practitioners.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">Research Statement</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">A short research statement of 500–800 words outlining your proposed research area, its significance, and your initial thoughts on methodology. This is discussed and developed at interview.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-surface border-t border-border py-16 px-6 text-center">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Start with the MPhil</h2>
      <p class="text-muted mb-8">The MPhil is a meaningful first step into research. Apply today and begin the process of becoming a research-active professional.</p>
      <div class="flex gap-4 justify-center flex-wrap">
        <a href="/apply" class="btn-primary">Apply now</a>
        <a href="/connect" class="btn-outline">Speak to us</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
